<text>Torsional bond

In molecular mechanics, torsional bond is a potential maintaining the relative orientation of two adjacent angular bonds that jointly own two atoms. Important in stereochemistry, e.g. modeling helical structures and maintaining planarity of benzene rings or peptide bonds. 


 
